<pdd-reason>Exposes deterministic prompt and user-story ambiguity linting with an explicitly opted-in advisory LLM pass.</pdd-reason>

<pdd-dependency>prompt_lint_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>
<pdd-dependency>checkup_apply_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>

% Write `pdd/commands/prompt.py`, implementing the shared `prompt_lint` command used by `pdd checkup lint`.

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Requirements
- Implement a `prompt_lint` Click command (not a top-level `pdd prompt` group).
- Accept an optional prompt TARGET and optional `--stories <directory>`; require at least one.
- Run `scan_prompt` and `scan_stories` deterministically without network access.
- Support `--json` machine-readable output and `--strict` warning escalation.
- Accept `--llm` to enable advisory LLM-assisted ambiguity review on top of the default deterministic scan. Without `--llm`, never invoke LLM or cloud-backed work.
- Explicitly document the read-only, advisory nature of the linter in the docstring and help texts.
- Preserve exit codes: 0 for clean, 1 for warnings, 2 for errors or strict warnings.
- Add vocabulary apply flags (restricted patch kinds: `vocabulary_line` and `vocabulary_section_create` only):
  - `--interactive` flag (required with `--apply`)
  - `--apply` flag (required with `--interactive`; delegates to `run_checkup_apply` from `pdd.checkup_apply` with vocabulary patches from lint findings)
  - `--dry-run` flag (diff preview only; no file writes)
  - `--force-apply` flag (apply even when deterministic errors exist)
  - When `--apply` is present without `--interactive`, MUST raise `click.UsageError` ("--apply requires --interactive") before running any lint scan.
  - When `--apply` and `--interactive` are both set, convert lint findings to `ApplyPatch` objects (`patch_kind` restricted to `vocabulary_line` or `vocabulary_section_create`) and pass to `run_checkup_apply`.

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/commands/prompt.py`
